description:
Each storyboard needs to consist of basically 5 plotpoints:
1) the user need (the problem)
2) the idea & building (the solution)
3) the trial & observation (the testing)
4) the insight & optimization (the learning and integration problems)
5) the new idea & building & resolution (the feature)


1) Thomas explains the user need to move the desk and keeping all items on it save
2) Aline is the voice of the customer with the problem and talks about it.
3) Fabian drills hole for drink holder. Bottles can now be placed safely into it. (documentary style) 
4) Thomas explains the solution of the user need. 
5) We see the finished product and a employee using it, carrying the desk with ease.
